<p>
<seg id=1> Palestinian President Arafat began his first official flight from Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=2> Gaza International Airport was opened just the previous day. </seg>
<seg id=3> On Wednesday, the security officials saw Arafat's plane taking off the runway for Paris. </seg>
<seg id=4> Israel took charge of the airport. Security. </seg>
<seg id=5> The agreement of offering land for peace signed recently by Israel and Palestine cleared the path for the use of Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=6> The Palestinian people thought that the airport symbolized a great improvement of their sovereign rights and Palestinian economic development. </seg>
</p>
